The paper deals with signal and matrix recovery from noisy measurements, which is a common problem in information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), numerical analysis (cs.NA), signal processing (cs.SP), and statistical learning (cs.SI). The use of truncated norm minimization and the exploration of the relationship between restricted isometry property and truncated sparse approximation property are also common topics in these sub-categories.
